race.description: The Big Screen Company Maiden Plate
race.comment: SOMERSAULT (10) looks well placed to break through at the fourth time of asking. The debut over 1000m was just fair but her past couple over this trip have been good when narrowly beaten. She should come on from those and had a fitness advantage on key rivals. Drawn well for Dee, she can stalk the speed and prove too strong late. SUPERGRACE (11) resumes. She was last seen running third in town at Sandown Lakeside having hinted at good ability prior. She should be ready to run well. KOKO (3) made nice improvement at her second start last time, beaten half a length over this route. She'll just need a touch of luck early from the wide gate. MISS MARANDA (6) ran well on debut in a good maiden at Pakenham over 1000m and should appreciate the extra furlong here. She draws well for an in-form Luke Currie. TOY QUEEN (12) was sound on debut although this is harder.
